<MELItem itemNbr="34-42-06" id="X-BOEING:FTID:81205.787.DDG.CU.MEL.2-34-42-06.1.2-34-42-06_FAA">
<Title>Automatic Dependent Surveillance-Broadcast (ADS-B) System</Title>
<MELSubItem itemNbr="34-42-06-01">
<Title>ADS-B Out Extended Squitter Transmissions</Title>
<DispatchCondition dispCondOptions="A" repairInterval="C" nbrInstalled="2" nbrRequired="0" opsIndicator="(O)">
<Title>Two Inoperative</Title>
<DispatchConditionRemarks>
<Para>May be inoperative provided authorization is obtained from ATC facilities having jurisdiction over planned route of flight. Refer to Section 4/ ADS-B SUPPLEMENT for details.</Para>
<Note>
<Para>Any ADS-B Out function that operates normally may be used.</Para>
</Note>
</DispatchConditionRemarks>
<DispatchProcedure>
<OperationProcedure>
<Para>The PIC must comply with the procedure established by Air Navigation Service Provider(s) when flying in ADS-B out airspace.</Para>
<Note>
<Para>Priority will be given to aircraft which are ADS-B equipped over non-equippent aircraft in the designated airspace and flight level assignments would be subjected to air traffic conditions and as required by Air Navigation Service Provider.</Para>
</Note>
</OperationProcedure>
</DispatchProcedure>
</DispatchCondition>
<DispatchCondition dispCondOptions="B" repairInterval="C" nbrInstalled="2" nbrRequired="1">
<Title>One Operative</Title>
<DispatchConditionRemarks>
<Para>One may be inoperative.</Para>
<Note>
<Para>Any ADS-B function that operates normally may be used.</Para>
</Note>
</DispatchConditionRemarks>
</DispatchCondition>
</MELSubItem>
</MELItem>
